# Harmony AI App Brief
@Overview: Open-source Android mobile app for AI character chat. Mobile frontend for Harmony Link ecosystem.
@Purpose:
- Mobile access to Harmony Link AI characters
- Chat with AI on Android devices
- Connected mode (Harmony Link/Cloud) + on-device AI
- Privacy-first with user-controlled backends
- Testing field for messenger integration
@Goals:
- Mobile AI Chat: Seamless conversations on Android
- Dual Backend: Self-hosted Link or Harmony Cloud
- On-Device AI: Limited offline with Executorch (up to 7B models)
- Privacy Control: Full data control with self-hosted
- Messenger Integration: WhatsApp/Telegram (future premium)
- Open Source: Community-driven, transparent
@Innovation: Mobile-first AI chat + flexible backends (privacy or convenience). On-device AI for offline. Messenger integration vision for everyday platforms.
@Users: Privacy-conscious users, Harmony Link users, power users, content creators, AI app developers.
@Reqs: Android primary (iOS community), React Native, Harmony Link APIs (WS/REST), SQLite persistence with sync, Executorch integration, Material Design 3, text/voice/image support, character memory.
@RecentUpdates[SDK+Presets]:
- Harmony Link backend migrated from go-openai to openai-go v3 SDK
- New Sampling Preset system: YAML preset files loaded from <dataDir>/presets/*.yaml
- Presets enable advanced LLM sampling control (typical_p, tfs, dry_*, etc.)
- App syncs preset name + extra params via WebSocket (not management API)
- DB migration 021 adds sampling_preset_name + extra_params to module config tables
- Extended params stored as JSON in extra_params column
- Precedence: explicit config > extraParams > preset values > library defaults
@RecentUpdates[Phase09]:
- New LLM API parameters from Phase 09 flow through sync pipeline to app
- Provider config parameters across 8 layers: migration → models → repos → sync → clients → frontend schemas
- Key-value-list field type for editing extra_params in UI
- Lifecycle Settings UI added to Harmony Link (not synced to app — autonomy controlled locally)
@RecentUpdates[ProviderExpansion]:
- xAI/Google/Anthropic providers added across all module types
- Model field unification: migration 000030 consolidates model columns
- 15 provider schemas in providerFieldSchemas.ts
- Dead module-specific schemas removed, merged into main provider schemas
- Movement module supports Google/xAI/Anthropic providers
- Shared isProviderConfigInUse() helper with UNION ALL
